      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hey there! It sounds like your lower back is feeling the brunt of the lift, which is a classic sign that your form is off, but don't worry, we can fix this! First, imagine your spine is a stack of goblin bricks; if you try to lift the whole stack with your back muscles, they'll crumble, but if you use your legs like a goblin's powerful legs, the bricks stay safe.\n\nWhen you deadlift, your legs should be doing all the heavy lifting, not your spine. Think of it like a goblin trying to carry a heavy sack of gold; they use their strong legs to scoot the sack forward, not their back. If your back is doing all the work, it's like a goblin trying to run a marathon while carrying the sack; they'll get tired and hurt very quickly.\n\nTo fix this, focus on keeping your back straight and your core tight, like a goblin's armor. When you start the lift, push your hips back and then drive through your heels, like a goblin pushing off the ground to jump over a puddle. If your back is doing all the work, it's like a goblin trying to jump by pulling",
