      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, no worries! The goblin bricks were just a clumsy metaphor, though I suppose even goblins have a hard time explaining anatomy without bringing up their own anatomy. Let's get straight to the point: your lower back is screaming because your **posterior chain** isn't firing correctly.\n\nThe **posterior chain** is essentially a long, muscular rope that runs down the back of your body, from the top of your spine all the way down to your heels. It includes your **glutes** (butt muscles), **hamstrings** (back of your thighs), **erector spinae** (the muscles running up your spine), and your **traps**. Think of it like a goblin's entire backside and legs fused into one super-strong unit; if you only use your spine (the middle part) instead of the whole chain, you're essentially trying to lift a heavy goblin by pulling on its neck instead of its legs.\n\nHere is exactly what you need to do to engage it safely:\n\n1.  **The Setup (The \"Goblin Crouch\"):** Before you even touch the bar, imagine you are sitting on a giant goblin throne. Your hips should be slightly lower than",
